This document studies definitions of risk, assets, threats, and vulnerabilities. 
Hypothetical Government Agency(HGA) is considered in the first half of the project, assets, vulnerabilities, and threats are identified.
Residual Asset Security Risk and Residual Vulnerability Security Risk is calculated and the necessary controls are suggested.
Security Risk Prevention, Risk Response, and Mixed Strategy are invoved and risk is again calculated considering these strategies are implemented.
The metrics are considered per 100 for the case of HGA.
For the second part of the project, a real-time company called Kshemin Innovations is considered where the value is calculated in Dollars.
The same risk calculations are calculated and necessary controls are suggested.
Finally, Cost-Benefit Analysis is calculated for each of the strategies involved.


